
2 March 1776. I visited the . . . Guards in the left and Center Division1 and . . . found all the Guards in Good OrderCapt. Lewis reported Eight oClock this Morning Five sail of Ships were Coming into Boston.2 . . . N.B. Joel Hewit of Col. Sargeants Regiment & Francis Offy of Col. Greytons Regt3 confined in the Main Guard at Cambridge for Mutiny & Disobedience of Orders.
